    "52": "Unable to open the Field dialog.",
    "53": "Displays a list of section view styles available in the current drawing file. The current style is highlighted. ",
    "54": "Displays the name of the section view style that is applied to section views you create.",
    "55": "User defined",
    "56": "Filters the contents of the Styles list. Click All Styles to display all section view styles available in the drawing file. Click Styles in use to display only the section view styles that are referenced by section views in the current drawing. ",
    "57": "Displays a preview image of the style that is selected in the Styles list. ",
    "58": "Sets the section view style selected in the Styles list as the current style. All new section views are created using this section view style. ",
    "59": "Displays the Create New Section View Style dialog box, in which you can define new section view styles. ",
    "60": "Displays the Modify Section View Style dialog box, in which you can modify section view styles. \nNote You cannot rename the section view styles Imperial24 and Metric50. ",
    "61": "Deletes the section view style selected in the Styles list. This button is not available if the style selected in the Styles list is currently in use by a section view. \nNote You cannot delete the section view styles Imperial24 and Metric50. ",
    "62": "Displays a list of detail view styles available in the current drawing file. The current syle is highlighted. ",
    "63": "Displays the name of the detail view style that is applied to detail views you create. ",
    "64": "Filters the contents of the Styles list. Click All Styles to display all detail view styles available in the drawing file. Click Styles in use to display only the detail view styles that are referenced by detail views in the current drawing. ",
    "65": "Displays a preview image of the style that is selected in the Styles list. ",
    "66": "Sets the detail view style selected in the Styles list as the current style. All new detail views are created using this detail view style. ",
    "67": "Displays the Create New Detail View Style dialog box, in which you can define new detail view styles. ",
    "68": "Displays the Modify Detail View Style dialog box, in which you can modify detail view styles. \nNote You cannot rename the detail view styles Imperial24 and Metric50. ",
    "69": "Deletes the detail view style selected in the Styles list. This button is not available if the style selected in the Styles list is referenced by a detail view in the current drawing. \nNote You cannot delete the detail view styles Imperial24 and Metric50. ",
    "70": "Names the new section view style. By default, the new style name is the Start With style name, prefixed by \"Copy of\". ",
    "71": "Specifies an existing section view style whose settings are the default for the new style. ",
    "72": "Displays the New Section View Style dialog box, in which you define the properties of the new section view style. ",
    "73": "Names the new detail view style. By default, the new style name is the Start With style name, prefixed by \"Copy of\". ",
    "74": "Specifies an existing detail view style whose settings are the default for the new style. ",
    "75": "Displays the New Detail View Style dialog box, in which you define the properties of the new detail view style. ",
    "76": "When selected, displays view labels on detail views.",
    "77": "Specifies the text style to use for the detail view label.",
    "78": "Displays the Text Style dialog, where you can create or modify text styles.",
    "79": "Specifies the color to use for the detail view label. If you click Select Color (at the bottom of the Color list), the Select Color dialog box is displayed. You can also enter a color name or number.",
    "80": "Specifies the size of the detail view label.",
    "81": "Specifies the placement of the detail view label, in relation to the detail view.",
    "82": "Specifies the gap between the edge of the detail view and the detail view label.",
    "83": "Specifies the default textual content for detail view labels. You typically use the following fields within detail view labels. \nViewDetailID - Evaluates to the detail view identifier. \nViewScale - Evaluates to the scale the detail is magnified to.  \nViewType - Always evaluates to \"detail\", when used in a detail view label. ",
    "84": "When selected, displays view labels on section views.",
    "85": "Sets the text style to use for the section view label. ",
    "86": "Displays the Text Style dialog, where you can create or modify text styles.",
    "87": "Sets the color to use for the section view label. If you click Select Color (at the bottom of the Color list), the Select Color dialog box is displayed. You can also enter a color name or number.",
    "88": "Sets the height of the section view label",
    "89": "Sets the placement of the section view label, in relation to the section view.",
    "90": "Sets the gap between the edge of the section view and the section view label.",
    "91": "Sets the default textual content for section view labels. You typically use the following fields within section view labels. \nViewScale - Evaluates to the scale settings of the section view. \nViewSectionEndId - Evaluates to the ending section line identifier. \nViewSectionStartId - Evaluates to the starting section line identifier. \nViewType - Always evaluates to \"section\", when used in a section view label. ",
    "92": "Specifies the text style to use for the detail boundary identifier.",
    "93": "Standard",
