    "157": "Modify Section View Style: %s",
    "193": "Displays the Text Style dialog, where you can create or modify text styles.",
    "194": "Specifies the color to use for the detail view identifier. If you click Select Color (at the bottom of the Color list), the Select Color dialog box is displayed. You can also enter a color name or number.",
    "195": "Specifies the height of the detail boundary identifier.",
    "196": "Places the identifier in a gap on the detail view boundary, as shown in the icon.",
    "197": "Places the identifier outside the detail view boundary, as shown in the icon.",
    "198": "Specifies the arrowhead to use on either side of the gap in the detail view boundary. This option is not available if the detail view identifier is placed outside the detail view boundary.",
    "199": "Specifies the color to use for the arrowhead. If you click Select Color (at the bottom of the Color list), the Select Color dialog box is displayed. You can also enter a color name or number. This option is not available if the detail view identifier is placed outside the detail view boundary.",
    "200": "Specifies the size of the arrowhead. This option is not available if the detail view identifier is placed outside the detail view boundary.",
    "201": "When selected, connects the detail boundary to the identifier with a leader, when the identifier is moved away from its default placement. ",
    "202": "Sets the text style to use for identifiers.",
    "203": "Sets the color to use for identifiers. If you click Select Color (at the bottom of the Color list), the Select Color dialog box is displayed. You can also enter a color name or number.",
    "204": "Sets the height of identifiers.",
    "205": "Sets the characters that must not be used as identifiers.",
    "206": "When selected, displays section line identifiers at all bends.",
    "207": "When selected, names end and bends with consecutive letters of the alphabet.",
    "208": "When selected, displays direction arrows at the end points of section lines.",
    "209": "Modify Detail View Style: %s",
    "210": "Identifier and Arrows",
    "211": "Sets the arrowhead type to use at the start of the section line.",
    "212": "Sets the arrowhead type to use at the end of the section line.",
    "213": "Cutting Plane",
    "214": "Sets the color to use for direction arrows. Both direction arrows uses the same color. If you click Select Color (at the bottom of the Color list), the Select Color dialog box is displayed. You can also enter a color name or number.",
    "215": "Sets the size of the arrowheads. You can select a typical size from the list, or enter any numeric value for the size. The program validates the value you enter to prevent you from specifying invalid values. ",
    "216": "Sets the length of the extension lines used by the direction arrows.",
    "217": "Sets the position and alignment of the section line identifier.",
    "218": "Sets the distance to offset the section line identifier from the position specified by the Identifier position setting.",
    "219": "Specifies whether the direction arrows should point towards the cutting plane or away from the cutting plane.",
    "220": "Sets the color for the detail boundary line. If you click Select Color (at the bottom of the Color list), the Select Color dialog box is displayed. You can also enter a color name or number.",
    "221": "Sets the linetype for the detail boundary line. If you click Other, the Select Linetype dialog box is displayed.",
    "222": "Sets the lineweight of the detail boundary.",
    "223": "Sets the cut lines on the models in detail views to be smooth. ",
    "224": "Displays a border around detail views and sets the cut lines on the models shown in detail views to be smooth. ",
    "225": "Displays a connection line between the detail boundary and the detail view boundary. Additionally, displays a border around detail views and sets the cut lines on the models shown in detail views to be smooth. ",
    "226": "Sets the cut lines on the models in detail views to be jagged. ",
    "227": "Sets the color for the detail view border. If you click Select Color (at the bottom of the Color list), the Select Color dialog box is displayed. You can also enter a color name or number.",
    "228": "Sets the linetype for the connection line. If you click Other, the Select Linetype dialog box is displayed.",
    "229": "Sets the lineweight of the detail view border.",
    "230": "Sets the color for the connection line. If you click Select Color (at the bottom of the Color list), the Select Color dialog box is displayed. You can also enter a color name or number.",
    "231": "Sets the linetype for the connection line. If you click Other, the Select Linetype dialog box is displayed.",
    "232": "Sets the lineweight of the connection line.",
    "233": "When selected, displays the end and bend line segments of the section line. ",
    "234": "Sets the color for the end and bend segments. All end and bend line segments use the same color. If you click Select Color (at the bottom of the Color list), the Select Color dialog box is displayed. You can also enter a color name or number.",
    "235": "Sets the linetype for the end and bend segments. All end and bend line segments use the same linetype. If you click Other, the Select Linetype dialog box is displayed.",
    "236": "Sets the lineweight of the end and bend segments. All end and bend line segments use the same lineweight.",
    "237": "Sets the length of the end segments.",
    "238": "Sets the length of the extension beyond the direction arrows.",
    "239": "Sets the length of the bend line segment on either side of the bend vertices.",
    "240": "When selected displays the line segments of the section line. ",
    "241": "Sets the color of plane line segments. All plane line segments use the same color. If you click Select Color (at the bottom of the Color list), the Select Color dialog box is displayed. You can also enter a color name or number.",
    "242": "Sets the linetype of plane line segments. All plane line segments use the same linetype. If you click Other, the Select Linetype dialog box is displayed.",
    "243": "Sets the lineweight of plane lines. All plane line segments use the same lineweight.",
    "244": "When selected, displays hatches to indicate components that are cut by the cutting plane.",
    "245": "Sets the hatch pattern to use for all hatches within section views.",
    "246": "Displays the Hatch Pattern Palette Dialog box, which allows you to select from ANSI, ISO, and other industry-standard hatch patterns. ",
    "247": "Sets the color to use for all hatches within section views. If you click Select Color (at the bottom of the Color list), the Select Color dialog box is displayed. You can also enter a color name or number.",
    "248": "Sets the background color for hatches within section views. Choose None to turn off the background color. If you click Select Color (at the bottom of the Color list), the Select Color dialog box is displayed. You can also enter a color name or number.",
    "249": "Expands or contracts the hatch pattern.",
    "250": "Sets the transparency level for the hatch. If you select ByLayer, the transparency level of the layer hatches are drawn on (MD_Hatching, by default) is indicated by the slider.",
    "251": "Sets a list of angles for use by hatches within the section view. The first component within the section view uses the first entry in the list, the second component uses the second entry and so on. The list must contain at least one angle. ",
    "252": "Adds new angle to end of list.",
    "253": "Deletes selected angle from list. The list must contain at least one angle.",
